2 Usage
*******

Language Server Protocol (LSP):

   • ‘C-c C-e’ (‘eglot’) starts an LSP client.
   • When ‘nael-lsp’ is autoloaded: ‘C-c C-l’ (‘lsp’) starts an
     alternative LSP client.
   • ‘C-h .’ (‘eldoc-doc-buffer’) displays the ElDoc documentation
     buffer showing tactic state and expected goal at point.

   Abbreviations:

   • ‘C-c C-a’ (‘abbrev-mode’) enables abbreviations.
   • ‘C-c C-k’ (‘nael-abbrev-help’) echoes abbreviations that expand to
     the character at point, or, if active, to the selected region.

   Emacs commands beyond Nael:

   • ‘C-c C-c’ (‘project-compile’) suggests builds the current project,
     suggesting ‘lake build’ as command.
   • ‘M-g i’ (‘imenu’) jumps to an interactively chosen definition in
     current buffer.
   • ‘M-;’ (‘comment-dwim’) toggles the active region as comment or, if
     no region is active, creates a comment at end of line.
   • ‘M-q’ (‘prog-fill-reindent-defun’) fills the string- or
     comment-paragraph at point, or reindents the point-surrounding
     code.


